            "answer_text": "Let P be the principal of the loan, and r be the interest rate. Then: P((1+r)\u00b3-1)/P((1+r)\u00b2-1)=381/234 (r+1)\u00b3-1/(r+1)\u00b2-1=381/234 (r+1)(r\u00b2+2r+1) - 1/(r\u00b2+2r+1)-1=381/234 r\u00b3+3r\u00b2+3r+1\u20131/r\u00b2+2r+1\u20131=\u201d \u201c r(r\u00b2+3r+3)/r(r+2)=381/234 234r\u00b2+702r+702=381r+762 234r\u00b2+321r-60=0 Using the quadratic formula, we get a positive value for r of 0.166666666666667, or 16.67% \u2026\u2026\u2026\u2026\u2026\u2026\u2026\u2026 ",
